  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN166-kilavi">parattaiyoṭu puṉalāṭiya talaimakaṉ <app><lem>talaimakaḷiṭaippukku</lem><rdg wit="#C7">talaimakaḷiṭampukku</rdg></app> ‘yāṉ āṭiṟṟilēṉ’ eṉṟu cūḷuṟṟāṉ eṉpatu kēṭṭa parattai taṉ <app><lem>pāṅkāyiṉār kēṭpac colliyatu</lem><rdg wit="#C7 #RKv">pāṅkikkuc coṟṟatatu</rdg></app>.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What the other woman, who had heard that HE, who has bathed in the flood with the other woman, had entered at HER place [and] made an oath “I did not bathe”, said so that her companions heard.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN166">
        <l><anchor n="1"/>naṉmaraṅ kuḻīiya naṉaimutir cāṭi</l>
        <l>paṉṉā ḷaritta kōo yuṭaippiṉ</l>
        <l>mayaṅkumaḻait tuvalaiyiṉ maṟukuṭaṉ paṉikkum</l>
        <l>paḻampa ṉelliṉ vēḷūr vāyi</l>
        <l>ṉaṟuvirai kaḷitta nāṟiṇar mālai</l>
        <l>poṟivari yiṉavaṇ <supplied>ṭūta</supplied>la kaḻiyu</l>
        <l>muyarpali peṟūu murukeḻu teyvam</l>
        <l>puṉaiyiruṅ katup<supplied>pi</supplied> ṉiṭukkat tōḷvayi</l>
        <l>ṉaṉaiyē ṉāyi ṉaṇaṅkuka veṉṉeṉa</l>
        <l>maṉaiyōṭ ṭēṟṟu makiḻna ṉāyiṉ</l>
        <l>yārkol vāḻi tōḻi nerunait</l>
        <l>tārpūṅ kaḷiṟṟi ṟalaippuṇai taḻīi</l>
        <l>vatuvai yīraṇip polinta nammoṭu</l>
        <l>putuvatu vanta kāvirik</l>
        <l>kōṭutōy malirniṟai yāṭi yōrē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>“The fearful deity that obtains high offerings, (7)</l>
        <l>which the bees in spotted striped groups pass by without filling themselves, (6)</l>
        <l>with garlands of fragrant clusters that are imbued with fragrant scents, (5)</l>
        <l>at the gate of Vēḷūr with much old paddy,</l>
        <l>where the streets become wet together by drops of diffuse rain, (3)</l>
        <l>like a breach in the toddy ladle that had scooped for many days (2)</l>
        <l>the jars in which the buds mature that had crowded on good trees, (1)</l>
        <l>if I have been like that, (9ab)</l>
        <l>by the side of the troublesome [girl] with decorated dark hair, (8)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">let it torment me!,” (9cd)</l>
        <l>− if the delightful man thus assures her in the house, (10)</l>
        <l>who is the one, oh friend, (11a-c)</l>
        <l>who bathed in the flooding profusion that touched the branches (15)</l>
        <l>of the Kāviri that had newly come (14)</l>
        <l>with us who shone with the moist decoration of a bride, (13)</l>
        <l>embracing as a raft the head of an elephant bull with flowers in garlands, (12)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">yesterday? (11d)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>

